<plot>The first Columbia Pictures short (not feature film) in Sepia Tone highlights Machito and His Rhumba Band. It opens with "Machito Yego," followed by "Tamo." Betty Reilly sings "Tierra Va Tamble", and a dance tea, dances to "The Thrill of a New Romance." For the finale, Machito plays the Spanish riff tune "Nague."</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?350213</url></doc>
